# Step 5: Build Logging & S3 Storage

**Phase:** 4 -- Build System
**Step:** 5 of 5
**Type:** Code implementation
**Depends on:** Step 4 (BuildRunner generates the logs that this step captures and stores), Phase 1 (S3 bucket for log storage)
**Blocks:** Phase 8 (Log streaming over WebSocket extends this step's subscriber pattern)

---

## Objective

Implement real-time build log capture, secret scrubbing, subscriber-based streaming, and S3 storage for completed build logs. Every build produces a log file that captures all stdout and stderr output from git, package manager, build tools, and Docker. The logs are scrubbed of secrets before being stored or streamed.

---

## Current State

The build log infrastructure needs to be built from scratch. The relevant integration points are:

1. **`packages/core/src/build/builder.ts`** -- The `BuildRunner` class executes shell commands that produce stdout/stderr output. This step adds an `onLog` callback and a `BuildLogger` to capture that output.

2. **`packages/core/src/build/cache.ts`** -- The S3 upload/download functions need implementation for both build cache (tarballs) and build logs (text files).

3. **`packages/shared/src/backend/aws/s3.ts`** -- Already fully implemented. `uploadToS3()` and `downloadFromS3()` are ready to use.

---

## Implementation Plan

### BuildLogger Class

Create a `BuildLogger` class that handles log accumulation, secret scrubbing, subscriber notification, and S3 upload. This can be defined at the top of `builder.ts` or in a new file if it grows large enough.

```typescript
// packages/core/src/build/builder.ts (or packages/core/src/build/build-logger.ts)

export class BuildLogger {
  private lines: string[] = [];
  private subscribers: Set<(line: string) => void> = new Set();
  private secretPatterns: RegExp[] = [];

  constructor(private deploymentId: string) {}

  /**
   * Add secret values that must be scrubbed from all log output.
   * Call this before the build starts with known secrets.
   */
  addSecrets(secrets: string[]): void {
    for (const secret of secrets) {
      if (secret && secret.length > 3) {
        // Escape regex special characters in the secret value
        const escaped = secret.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\]\\]/g, "\\$&");
        this.secretPatterns.push(new RegExp(escaped, "g"));
      }
    }
  }

  /**
   * Subscribe to real-time log output.
   * Returns an unsubscribe function.
   */
  subscribe(callback: (line: string) => void): () => void {
    this.subscribers.add(callback);
    return () => this.subscribers.delete(callback);
  }

  /**
   * Log a line. Scrubs secrets, stores, and notifies subscribers.
   */
  log(line: string): void {
    const scrubbed = this.scrub(line);
    this.lines.push(scrubbed);
    for (const sub of this.subscribers) {
      try {
        sub(scrubbed);
      } catch {
        // Subscriber errors should not break the build
      }
    }
  }

  /**
   * Log a section header for visual separation in logs.
   */
  section(title: string): void {
    this.log(`\n--- ${title} ---\n`);
  }

  /**
   * Get all accumulated log lines as a single string.
   */
  getFullLog(): string {
    return this.lines.join("\n");
  }

  /**
   * Upload the complete log to S3.
   */
  async uploadToS3(bucket: string, projectId: string): Promise<string> {
    const key = `${projectId}/builds/${this.deploymentId}/build.log`;
    await uploadToS3(bucket, key, this.getFullLog());
    return key;
  }

  /**
   * Scrub secrets from a log line.
   */
  private scrub(line: string): string {
    let result = line;

    // Scrub known secret values from env_vars
    for (const pattern of this.secretPatterns) {
      result = result.replace(pattern, "***REDACTED***");
    }

    // Scrub git clone URLs with tokens
    result = result.replace(
      /https:\/\/x-access-token:[^@]+@github\.com/g,
      "https://github.com",
    );

    // Scrub common secret patterns
    result = this.scrubCommonPatterns(result);

    return result;
  }

  /**
   * Scrub common secret patterns that might appear in build output.
   */
  private scrubCommonPatterns(line: string): string {
    let result = line;

    // AWS access keys (AKIA...)
    result = result.replace(/AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}/g, "***REDACTED***");

    // Generic API key patterns (key=..., token=..., secret=...)
    result = result.replace(
      /(api[_-]?key|token|secret|password|passwd|credential)[=:]\s*['"]?[^\s'"]+['"]?/gi,
      "$1=***REDACTED***",
    );

    // PostgreSQL connection strings
    result = result.replace(
      /postgresql:\/\/[^:]+:[^@]+@/g,
      "postgresql://***:***@",
    );

    // Generic bearer tokens
    result = result.replace(
      /Bearer\s+[A-Za-z0-9\-._~+/]+=*/g,
      "Bearer ***REDACTED***",
    );

    return result;
  }
}
```

---

### Integration with BuildRunner

The `BuildRunner` must use the `BuildLogger` to capture all output:

#### 1. Initialize the logger at build start

```typescript
async run(): Promise<{ imageTag: string; durationMs: number }> {
  const buildLogger = new BuildLogger(this.options.deploymentId);

  // Load project secrets for scrubbing
  const secrets = await this.loadProjectSecrets();
  buildLogger.addSecrets(secrets);

  // Add the installation token to secrets (so it gets scrubbed from clone URL)
  const token = await getInstallationToken(this.options.installationId);
  buildLogger.addSecrets([token]);

  // Connect the onLog callback if provided
  if (this.options.onLog) {
    buildLogger.subscribe(this.options.onLog);
  }

  // ... pipeline execution ...
}
```

#### 2. Capture command output

Wrap all `execFile` calls to pipe stdout/stderr through the logger:

```typescript
private async execAsync(
  cmd: string,
  args: string[],
  options: { cwd?: string },
  logger: BuildLogger,
): Promise<void> {
  return new Promise<void>((resolve, reject) => {
    const proc = spawn(cmd, args, {
      cwd: options.cwd,
      stdio: ["ignore", "pipe", "pipe"],
    });

    proc.stdout?.on("data", (data: Buffer) => {
      const lines = data.toString("utf-8").split("\n");
      for (const line of lines) {
        if (line.trim()) logger.log(line);
      }
    });

    proc.stderr?.on("data", (data: Buffer) => {
      const lines = data.toString("utf-8").split("\n");
      for (const line of lines) {
        if (line.trim()) logger.log(line);
      }
    });

    proc.on("close", (code) => {
      if (code === 0) resolve();
      else reject(new Error(`Command '${cmd} ${args.join(" ")}' exited with code ${code}`));
    });

    proc.on("error", reject);
  });
}
```

Use `child_process.spawn()` instead of `execFile()` for streaming. `spawn()` gives us readable streams for stdout/stderr that we can pipe through the logger line by line. `execFile()` buffers all output and only returns it when the process exits, which prevents real-time streaming.

#### 3. Add section headers for each pipeline step

```typescript
buildLogger.section("Cloning repository");
await this.cloneRepo(buildDir, buildLogger);

buildLogger.section("Detecting framework");
const framework = await this.detectOrReadConfig(buildDir);
buildLogger.log(`Framework: ${framework.framework}, Mode: ${framework.nextMode ?? "n/a"}`);

buildLogger.section("Restoring build cache");
await this.restoreCache(buildDir, packageManager, buildLogger);

buildLogger.section("Installing dependencies");
await this.installDependencies(buildDir, packageManager, buildLogger);

buildLogger.section("Running build");
await this.runBuildCommand(buildDir, framework, buildLogger);

buildLogger.section("Building Docker image");
const imageTag = await this.buildDockerImage(buildDir, buildLogger);

buildLogger.section("Saving build cache");
await this.saveCache(buildDir, packageManager, buildLogger);

buildLogger.section("Build complete");
```

#### 4. Upload log to S3 in the finally block

```typescript
} finally {
  // Upload build log to S3 (even on failure)
  try {
    const s3Key = await buildLogger.uploadToS3(S3_BUCKET, this.options.projectId);
    await this.options.db
      .update(deployments)
      .set({ buildLogS3Key: s3Key })
      .where(eq(deployments.id, this.options.deploymentId));
  } catch (err) {
    logger.warn({ err }, "Failed to upload build log to S3");
  }

  // Clean up build directory
  await this.cleanup(buildDir);
}
```

