## Security: Secret Scrubbing Patterns

The following patterns are scrubbed from all build log output:

| Pattern | Example | Replacement |
|---------|---------|-------------|
| Exact env var secret values | `sk_live_abc123` | `***REDACTED***` |
| Git clone tokens | `https://x-access-token:ghs_xxx@github.com` | `https://github.com` |
| AWS access keys | `AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE` | `***REDACTED***` |
| API key assignments | `api_key=abc123` | `api_key=***REDACTED***` |
| PostgreSQL connection strings | `postgresql://user:pass@host` | `postgresql://***:***@host` |
| Bearer tokens | `Bearer eyJhbGciOi...` | `Bearer ***REDACTED***` |

The exact env var values (from the `env_vars` table where `is_secret=true`) are loaded and scrubbed first, then generic patterns are applied. This ensures project-specific secrets are caught even if they don't match a generic pattern.

---

## Verification

### Build Logging

- [ ] `BuildLogger.log(line)` stores the line and notifies all subscribers
- [ ] `BuildLogger.section(title)` adds a formatted section header
- [ ] `BuildLogger.subscribe(callback)` receives real-time log lines
- [ ] `BuildLogger.subscribe()` returns an unsubscribe function that stops notifications
- [ ] `BuildLogger.getFullLog()` returns all accumulated lines joined with newlines
- [ ] Subscriber errors do not break the build (caught and ignored)

### Secret Scrubbing

- [ ] Known env var secret values are replaced with `***REDACTED***`
- [ ] Git clone URLs with `x-access-token` are scrubbed
- [ ] AWS access key patterns (`AKIA...`) are scrubbed
- [ ] API key assignment patterns (`api_key=...`) are scrubbed
- [ ] PostgreSQL connection string passwords are scrubbed
- [ ] Bearer token patterns are scrubbed
- [ ] Short values (3 chars or fewer) are not used as scrub patterns (to avoid false positives)

### S3 Storage

- [ ] Build log is uploaded to S3 with key `{projectId}/builds/{deploymentId}/build.log`
- [ ] The `build_log_s3_key` field on the deployment record is updated after upload
- [ ] Log upload happens in the `finally` block (even for failed builds)
- [ ] Log upload failure is non-fatal (warning logged)

### Build Cache (cache.ts)

- [ ] `saveCache()` uploads a buffer to the correct S3 key
- [ ] `restoreCache()` downloads a buffer from S3
- [ ] `restoreCache()` returns `null` when no cache exists (first build)
- [ ] Tarball creation produces a valid gzipped tar archive
- [ ] Tarball extraction recreates the original directory structure

### Integration

- [ ] `BuildRunner.run()` uses `BuildLogger` throughout the entire pipeline
- [ ] All shell command output (stdout + stderr) flows through the logger
- [ ] Section headers appear in the correct order in the final log
- [ ] The `onLog` callback in `BuildRunnerOptions` receives real-time scrubbed output
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes with no errors
